    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1889-02-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1889-02-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="220" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Preston</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1889-02-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 18,
                                    1889</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have your telegrams of the 16th and 18th instant requesting this
                            Department to order the detention of the <hi rend="italic">Carondelet</hi> at Newport News and the <hi rend="italic">Conserva</hi> at New York. In accordance with your previous
                            requests <pb facs="0650" n="528" xml:id="pg_528"/> full opportunity has
                            been given for application to the judicial and customs authorities for
                            investigation of facts in relation to both these vessels. The
                            nationality and ownership of the <hi rend="italic">Conserva</hi>, and
                            the destination and objects of the cargo of the <hi rend="italic">Carondelet</hi>, have been properly made the subject of
                            investigation and decision by the officials of the appropriate
                            Departments of this Government, and nothing has been brought to my
                            knowledge which gives me authority to overrule, or ground to question
                            their action in the premises.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
